**`/api/upload/csv/route.ts`** — Sequential loop with per-item DB queries:

```typescript
for (const prop of properties) {
  const existing = await prisma.property.findFirst({ where: { addressNormalized } });
  // ... then creates one at a time
  const property = await prisma.property.create({ ... });
  await prisma.activity.create({ ... });
}
```

**Problem:** For 500 imported properties = 1000+ sequential DB calls.

**Fix:** Batch operations with `createMany` and use `transaction` for atomicity:

```typescript
const addressNormList = properties.map(p => normalizeAddress(p.addressRaw));
const existing = await prisma.property.findMany({
  where: { addressNormalized: { in: addressNormList } }
});
const existingSet = new Set(existing.map(p => p.addressNormalized));

const toCreate = properties.filter(p => 
  !existingSet.has(normalizeAddress(p.addressRaw))
);

// Batch create in chunks of 100
const BATCH_SIZE = 100;
for (let i = 0; i < toCreate.length; i += BATCH_SIZE) {
  const batch = toCreate.slice(i, i + BATCH_SIZE);
  await prisma.$transaction(async (tx) => {
    await tx.property.createMany({ data: batch.map(p => ({ ... })) });
  });
}
```

---

**`/api/activity/export/route.ts`** — No pagination or limits:

```typescript
const activities = await prisma.activity.findMany({
  // No take() limit!
  orderBy: { createdAt: "desc" },
});
```

**Fix:** Add `take: 10000` or implement streaming for large exports.

---

**Repeated `new Date()` calls across multiple rows:**

```typescript
const rows = activities.map((a) => [
  new Date(a.createdAt).toLocaleDateString(),  // called twice per row
  new Date(a.createdAt).toLocaleTimeString(),
```

**Fix:** Extract timestamp once:

```typescript
const rows = activities.map((a) => {
  const ts = new Date(a.createdAt);
  return [ts.toLocaleDateString(), ts.toLocaleTimeString(), ...];
});
```

---

**`/api/backup/route.ts`** — Loads entire DB into memory:

```typescript
const [properties, users, activities, ...] = await Promise.all([
  prisma.property.findMany({ include: { contacts: { include: { emails: true, phones: true } }, notes: true, photos: true } }),
  // All 8 queries load full datasets
]);
```

**Problem:** With thousands of properties/photos, this can exhaust memory.

**Fix:** Stream responses or use cursor-based pagination for backup generation.

---

**`/api/properties/[id]/photos/route.ts`** — Sequential delete in DELETE handler:

```typescript
const photos = await prisma.photo.findMany({ where: { propertyId: id } });
for (const photo of photos) {
  await prisma.photo.delete({ where: { id: photo.id } });  // N queries
}
```

**Fix:** Single `deleteMany`:

```typescript
await prisma.photo.deleteMany({ where: { propertyId: id } });
```

